      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_808619e790f69c520eefe1f6c89c7825">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Notebooks, memorabilia, a small amount of correspondence, and other items make up the papers of Edward H. Knight (1877-1974, Y. 1898). Almost all of the materials related to Knight's year at Yale College, 1897-1898. Included are nine books of Knight's notes taken on the lectures of William Lyon Phelps, Oliver H. Richardson, William Graham Sumner, and Arthur M. Wheeler. There are also notes taken by Albert A. Palmer (Y. 1901) of Wheeler's lectures in 1899, and a history paper on Aaron Burr written by Palmer. The correspondence consists of letters concerning Knight's admission to Yale College and one family letter. In addition to these materials, the Papers contain a genealogy and short autobiography of Knight, and selected Yale memorabilia.</p>
         <p>These papers were given to Yale University by Edward H. Knight in 1943.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9db018d21ca00f27ac77d6878e112ebf">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Edward H. Knight: Indianapolis, Indiana city attorney, 1927-1930; corporation counsel, 1930-1935; assistant prosecuting attorney of Marion County, 1935-1939; corporation counsel, 1939- .</p>
      </bioghist>
